---
description: Targeted deterministic TDD scope for data pipeline scripts
globs:
  - "scripts/*.py"
  - "tests/**/*.py"
  - ".github/workflows/ci.yml"
alwaysApply: true
---

- Default workflow for script logic changes: write or update tests first, then implement, then run `pytest`.
- Mandatory test areas for this repo:
  - schema and contract validation behavior (required fields, status/shape guards, strict/fallback semantics)
  - deterministic parsing/transforms (date parsing, numeric normalization, mapping/aggregation, derived metrics)
  - fallback/unavailable behavior and metadata fields for failed extraction paths
- Non-required or discouraged test areas:
  - live endpoint availability and real external API responses
  - brittle HTML/PDF content details that change frequently upstream
  - full generated data snapshots unless fixture input is intentionally stable
- Keep tests deterministic:
  - mock or monkeypatch network, file I/O boundaries, and current time where behavior depends on clocks
  - prefer small synthetic fixtures over large captured payloads
  - assert stable contracts and core semantics, not volatile prose or formatting details
- Test style standards:
  - use clear arrange -> act -> assert structure
  - one behavior focus per test, descriptive test names
  - avoid sleeps, retries, and time-dependent race assumptions
